  "specialRules": [
    "1. Everyone is at the center of their room except the victim",
    "2. All occupied rooms have 180degrees rotational symmetry (around their center occupant).",
    "3. All unoccupied rooms have exactly one black hole. All black holes are in unoccupied rooms. All black holes are shown."
  ],
  "rules": [
    "Add borders to the grid to satisfy all special rules and all clues.",
    "Place everyone on the grid according to their clue to find the murderer. He was in a region alone with the victim.",
    "Only 1 person per row and per column.",
    "\"Beside\" means in the same room and orthogonally adjacent."
  ],
  "clues": [
    "A (Woman - Agatha). She was in a room that shared a diagonnal corner with Ernest's room.",
    "B (Man - Bradford). He was in a room that had at least a 2x2 region.",
    "C (Woman - Celeste). Her room shared the same highest row as Ernest's room. (They both reach the same north-most row)",
    "D (Man - Duncan). His room area was smaller than Helen's room.",
    "E (Man - Ernest). He was in a room with the same total height as 2 other populated rooms.",
    "F (Man - Finnegan). His room area was the same as only one other room area.",
    "G (Man - George). His room shares a border with Celeste's room.",
    "H (Woman - Helen). Her room shares borders with 3 other populated rooms.",
    "V (Woman - Virginia). The victim. She was alone with the murderer."
  ],
